column11:
  Single particle distribution function of plasma particles has been derived
from the first member of the Bogoliubov-Born-Green-Kirkwood-Yvon (BBGKY)
hierarchy utilising the pair correlation function evaluated in \cite{kn:ab1}
from the second member of the BBGKY hierarchy. This distribution function may
be employed to probe the thermodynamic properties of the weakly inhomogeneous
plasma systems.
